release.name: v1.2.0
release.body:
## What's Changed
* Add ContainerDefinition aware of active profiles by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/154
* Refactor Alias resolution into own object by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/155
* Introduce AbstractContainerFactory by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/156
* Add ability to get AC version in-app by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/157


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/compare/v1.1.0...v1.2.0

issue.title: Add functionality to improve creating different ContainerFactory implementations

milestone.title: v1.2 Release
milestone.description: A release that improves the ability to add a backing Container to the library.

issue.body: There is currently duplicated functionality between the 2 existing ContainerFactory implementations. There's a strong likelihood that future implementations will require similar types of functionality. The different pieces of code duplicated between the two implementations should be refactored into a parent class or a separate service that implementations can compose.

issue.title: Add a ContainerDefinition implementation that is profile aware

milestone.title: v1.2 Release
milestone.description: A release that improves the ability to add a backing Container to the library.

issue.body: It would be useful to have a `ContainerDefinition` decorator that knew what profiles were active and then when you retrieved definitions that were profile aware only those definitions matching the active profiles would be included. This type of design would allow all ContainerFactory implementations to reuse profile resolution code and would also allow tooling and other parts of the codebase use the same functionality without it being tied to a ContainerFactory the way it currently is.
